Land use is dominated by arable farming.Surveying reveals a high proportion of{cereals}(wheat and barley) with lesser amounts of{sugar {beet,potatoes,oil seed rape and peas.}
A detailed survey of fields during July 1985 revealed the following crop-cover details: {Wheat }50% {Barley }23% {Sugar Beet }8% { Peas }7.5% {Oil-Seed Rape }4.5% {Potatoes }2%
The remaining 5% of the agricultural land was occupied by{Pasture.}
The area around Grayingham was almost totally devoted to cereals, whilst further north, a more mixed crop pattern was recognised.
